<h1 class="hero-h">A 15-item AI rollout checklist <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">for CEOs.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">If you are the CEO and you are about to greenlight an AI rollout, run through these 15 boxes first. Each one is a place where rollouts predictably stall. Get them right at the start and you save yourself 60 days of recovery later.</p>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Before kickoff</span><h2 class="h2">Five boxes — strategy &amp; commitment</h2><ul class="checklist"><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>I have written down, in one paragraph, what this AI initiative is meant to achieve.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>I have named one person — not a committee — as the AI lead.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>I have protected 8-12 hours/week of that person's calendar for at least the next 90 days.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>I have a budget envelope set, even if rough, and the AI lead knows what it is.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>I personally will spend 2 hours/week on this for the next 90 days.</span></li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">In the first 30 days</span><h2 class="h2">Five boxes — scoping &amp; setup</h2><ul class="checklist"><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>We have audited current AI usage at the company (paid licenses + shadow IT) and know what's already happening.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>We have ranked candidate workflows by leverage and picked the top 3 to ship.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>We have a named workflow owner for each of the 3 — different humans, each accountable for their workflow.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>We have selected and provisioned an enterprise-tier AI platform for everyone in the affected workflows.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>We have written down data-handling rules — what can go into AI tools, what cannot.</span></li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">By day 90</span><h2 class="h2">Five boxes — production &amp; governance</h2><ul class="checklist"><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>At least one workflow is in production daily use, with measurable impact recorded.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>Workflows 2 and 3 are shipped or visibly close.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>A one-page AI policy is published and the team knows what it says.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>I have reviewed real outputs from the AI workflows — not slides about them.</span></li><li class="check-item"><span class="check-box"></span><span>The AI lead has Q2 priorities and a backlog for what ships next.</span></li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Anti-patterns</span><h2 class="h2">If any of these is true, stop and fix</h2><ul class="ul"><li>You cannot name the AI lead in one second.</li><li>The "AI committee" has more than 3 people on it.</li><li>Workflows have been "planned" for more than 6 weeks without shipping.</li><li>You are personally using AI tools rarely or never. (Leaders who do not use it cannot lead its adoption.)</li><li>You are confused about whether the AI rollout's purpose is productivity, transformation, headcount reduction, or PR. Pick one.</li></ul></div></section>

